        • history

          java.util.LinkedList<com.anylogic.engine.Pair<java.lang.String,​Attempt>> history
          Holds the last 500 commands ran by the user, in chronological order (i.e., the first item is the most recently run command).

          Implemented as a list of Pair objects with the command as the first value and the Attempt as the second value.

          For example, to get the code used in the most recent command: history.get(0).getFirst()

          And to get the Attempt used in the most recent command: history.get(0).getSecond()



          Provided as reference for the end-user; for example, if they execute multiple commands sequentially and want the outputs without having to create an object for each call.

        • pythonExecPath

        • redirectPyOutput

          boolean redirectPyOutput
          Whether to redirect output coming from Python to the AnyLogic console.

          If true, anything sent by Python to the standard output (e.g., print statements) or non-halting standard error (e.g., warnings) will be printed to the AnyLogic console.

          When viewed from the developer panel, standard output will be printed in green and standard error will be printed in red.
